Birch was born in [[Newport, Wales|Newport]], [[Monmouthshire (historic)|Monmouthshire]]. A right-winger, he began his career with [[Ebbw Vale F.C.|Ebbw Vale]] and joined [[Norwich City F.C.|Norwich]] in 1949. In 1950 he joined [[Newport County A.F.C.|Newport County]] and made 142 [[Football League]] appearances for the club, scoring 28 goals. In 1954 he moved to [[Colchester United F.C.|Colchester United]] and later to [[Spalding United F.C.|Spalding United]].<ref name=ATZ>{{Cite web |url=http://www.neilbrown.newcastlefans.com/player2/cliffbirch.html |title=Cliff Birch |website=Post War English & Scottish Football League A–Z Player's Database |publisher=Neil Brown |accessdate=8 November 2017}}</ref>
